  , issueCommentBody =
      "If we rebase the Python driver onto `asyncio` then `run`, `connect` and probably cursors would become something like this:\r\n```\r\ndef run(*args, *kwargs):\r\n    loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()\r\n    result = arun(*args, *kwargs)\r\n    loop.run_until_complete(result)\r\n    return result.result()\r\n```\r\nand similarly for the others.  That is, they will automatically play nice with async stuff under the scenes, so you don't need to use `arun` and `aconnect` and the like unless actually necessary."
